comments.body:
OK, that was rough.  Tests setting a custom CONTAINERS_CONF have failed.  What I observed at some point was that the cleanup processes did not fire in those cases.

It turned out that Podman started conmon with the working directory pointing to the runtime bundle.  The changed working directory ultimately broke resolving relative paths (e.g., for env variables such as CONTAINERS_CONF).  Since we set the bundle path explicitly, we don't need to do that and let conmon have the same working dir.

@mheon this should explain why cleanups do not happen sometimes.
